&nbsp;', 'Welcome to the magical city of moose, mountains, and snow. Anchorage, Alaska is balanced between the Chugach Mountains and Cook Inlet, known for its remarkable natural beauty and fun out-of-doors culture. From hiking and fishing in the summer to dogsledding and skiing in the winter, there’s always adventure to be found. The city also boasts a vibrant cultural scene, with a variety of museums, art galleries, and performing arts venues to explore. This land surrounded by mountain peaks used to be occupied by an icy glacier; now, it’s a unique town where you can shop at the same place that you go fishing.', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d06798ae6eda4bf2735e_anchorage-c1.jpeg', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d06798ae6ea8cdf27362_anchorage-c2.jpeg', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63ca0aabed101e2274342f82_63c9ddb96dddae08d0ac69a8_63c9d6500c3d4b2fbeda7ac6_ExploroAd.jpeg', 'https://media-dev.exploro.com/inflight-media/anchorage-about-banner.jpg', ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d06798ae6e08c0f27363_anchorage-overview.jpeg','https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d06798ae6eaf31f2735f_anchorage-c3.jpeg','https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d06798ae6ee1fff27364_anchorage-c4.jpeg'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d06798ae6e84bef27360_anchorage-getting.jpeg','<p id="">If you are planning to stay within the city center, you can walk to see as much as you can. However, if you want to take a trip outside the city, it would be easy to rent a car or using rideshares. Much of the transportation in Alaska is by plane, so you might consider looking into airfare if you want to travel around the state.</p>'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d06798ae6e8099f2735d_anchorage-fnb.jpeg','<p id="">Extended daylight hours during the summer combined with Alaskan soil provide Anchorage with fresh-grown fruits and vegetables, and the seafood here is recommended around the world. The city is conscious of environmental sustainability from both ocean and land harvests, with lots of ethically sourced food. And of course, you can’t leave Alaska without trying the Pacific Chinook salmon; Alaska’s state fish.</p>'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d06798ae6e38ccf27361_anchorage-facts.jpeg','<p id="">On a clear day, you can see up to 6 different mountain ranges from Anchorage: the Aleutian, Chugach, Kenai, Talkeetna and Tordrillo.Alaska’s Mount Denali-- which you can spot all the way from Anchorage if the weather is good-- is actually taller from base to summit than Mount Everest, with a greater rise!Mount Denali continues to a few centimeters each year due to shifting plates in the earth. Anchorage is possibly the only city in the state of Alaska in which you can surf, thanks to its high tidal waves.Anchorage weather is not as extreme as some think. Average daytime temperatures range from 5 degrees to 78 degrees, and it gets quite warm in the summers.There are over 100 languages spoken just within the borders of in this city!</p>'], ARRAY['Hotel Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum'], ARRAY['Restaurant Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor i