The air station was dramatically downsized in the early 21st century, resulting in a sizable population reduction. The current population of around 2,500 residents now works closely with the fishing and tourism industry, which has been increasing significantly in the past decade – especially for whale watching.', 'Andenes is a small fishing village on the tip of the northern island of Andoya. The picturesque views of the ocean meeting mountains in a life with little modern-world interruption makes you feel on the tip of the earth. But there is not a lack of things to do and see in Andenes. The city and its island are an outdoor enthusiast’s dream with activities available for every season, and the ability to experience them during some of the world’s most exciting phenomena like the midnight sun, polar night, and the Northern Lights.', '', '', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63ca0aabed101e2274342f82_63c9ddb96dddae08d0ac69a8_63c9d6500c3d4b2fbeda7ac6_ExploroAd.jpeg', 'https://media-dev.exploro.com/inflight-media/andenes-about-banner.jpg', ARRAY['','',''], ARRAY['','<p id="">A vehicle will be necessary to take advantage of your stay and explore the island of Andoya.However, suppose you plan to stay local to the city of Andenes. In that case, it is easily accessible by walking and the local taxi service.</p>'], ARRAY['','<p id="">To truly get the northern Norway experience, try some local delicacies served at many restaurants in the town of Andenes. Look for dishes that have lamb, monkfish, local shellfish, salmon, and even reindeer.Believe it or not, reindeer stew is a local favorite.</p>'], ARRAY['','<p id="">Andenes is in the municipality of Andoy and is known as the "Whale Kingdom of the North."Midnight Sun, resulting in 24 hours of light a day, can be experienced in Andenes from May 19th – July 25th each year.Polar Night, is experienced in Andenes from November 25th to January 28th. It is when the sun does not rise above the horizon resulting in darkness 24 hours a day.The village of Andenes is less than one square mile in length.The island of Andoya is the only place in Norway where dinosaur fossils have been discovered.There are pine trees in Andenes and its island of Andoya that are over 700 years old.</p>'], ARRAY['Hotel Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum'], ARRAY['Restaurant Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum'], ARRAY['Attraction Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum'], ARRAY[''], 2, 1, 14, 1);















&nbsp;', 'As one of the oldest cities in the US, Baltimore (pronounced ‘Bawlmer’ or ‘Baldamore’ by most locals), features a fascinating blend of history and innovation, art and science - and, of course, lots and lots of seafood. The dazzling array of new and aging architecture reflects the city’s grounding in both the past and the present. Baltimore is also considered a ’city of neighborhoods.’ Visitors can explore more than 250 neighborhoods within the city; each with it sown unique culture, shopping, and dining experience. Check out the museums, parks, historical sites, and Baltimore’s expansive 7-mile brick waterfront promenade. From the original penning of ‘The Star Spangled Banner’ here in 1814, to its ongoing economic and residential growth today, Baltimore was and continues to be a quintessentially American city.', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d06725c8366f91e487cb_baltimore-c1.jpeg', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d06725c8362f00e487ce_baltimore-c2.jpeg', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63ca0aabed101e2274342f82_63c9ddb96dddae08d0ac69a8_63c9d6500c3d4b2fbeda7ac6_ExploroAd.jpeg', 'https://media-dev.exploro.com/inflight-media/baltimore-maryland.mp4', ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d06725c836170fe487ca_baltimore-overview.jpeg','https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d06725c836077ee487cc_baltimore-c3.jpeg','https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d06725c8361b65e487c9_baltimore-c4.jpeg'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d06725c83658a0e487cd_baltimore-getting.jpeg','<p id="">Transportation options here vary depending on your preferences. The light rail line is a solid choice, particularly when coming from BWI Airport, but note that the line only runs North-to-South. Buses service a much larger range of destinations, though they aren’t always as timely/reliable. Ride-sharing is quick and convenient in a pinch. Many locals suggest biking when the weather is nice, and a fun alternative is to rent an electric scooter to zip around town on! Keep in mind that bike lanes aren’t always provided, so be alert when braving the busy downtown traffic.</p>'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d06725c8367fa6e487c7_baltimore-fnb.jpeg','<p id="">If you’re new around town you ought to know: Baltimore is top-of-the-line when it comes to seafood, caught locally in the Bay. Besides snacking on Baltimore’s famous crab cakes, you can stroll through the iconic Little Italy neighborhood for some fabulous traditional cuisine, or stop by Lexington Market for a quick bite. For those on a budget, try a perfectly fried “chicken box,” a local favorite. And while you’re exploring Baltimore’s Polish-inspired culinary history, be sure to try a classic Natty Boh (the local nickname for National Bohemian Beer), a traditional lager introduced back in 1885.</p>'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d06725c836905fe487c8_baltimore-facts.jpeg','<p id="">Francis Scott Key wrote the lyrics for the Star-Spangled Banner here during the Battle of Baltimore in the War of 1812.Baltimore hosts the largest free arts festival in the U.S. called Artscape.John Hopkins University, Notre Dame, Morgan State University, and other prestigious universities call Baltimore home.Baltimore’s NFL team was named The Ravens in honor of Edgar Allen Poe and his famous poem, “The Raven.”In addition to the nation’s first Catholic cathedral, Baltimore is home to all kinds of other ‘firsts,’ like the first dental school in the world; the first railroad in the nation; the first ever 6-pack of beer; the first manned balloon, which was ridden by a 13-year-old; and the first ever telegraph message, sent between Baltimore and Washington, DC.The BWI Airport hosts its own 12.5 mile hiking and biking trail, for those travelers who have a bit (or a lot) of extra time and energy.Baltimore’s climate is warm during spring and fall. Summers are hot, with frequent thunderstorms. Winters are relatively mild with occasional snow.</p>'], ARRAY['Hotel Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum'], ARRAY['Restaurant Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum'], ARRAY['Attraction Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum'], ARRAY[''], 2, 1, 6, 1);




Locals are proud of Barranquilla’s personality, delicious food, and variety of great activities. Residents of this diverse city are also known as "Barranquilleros." Visitors can spot them for their relaxed but outgoing and friendly attitude. Interestingly, Barranquilla is generally called "Curramba" by its residents and Colombians, which means "party.', 'Located in the beautiful country of Colombia, Barranquilla is the perfect destination for a unique vacation. Colombia is bordered by both the Caribbean Sea and the Pacific Ocean, and by South American countries Venezuela, Brazil, Ecuador, Peru, and Panama. The city of Barranquilla is situated between the mouth of the Caribbean Sea and the Magdalena River, making waterfront views easy to access from any direction. Founded in 1629, Barranquilla has a rich history and culture. The city is known for its colorful Carnival celebrations, which are among the most famous in the world.&nbsp;', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d09a892800cb5bb9bc61_barranquilla-c1_0.jpeg', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d09a892800f0c0b9bc64_barranquilla-c2_0.jpeg', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63ca0aabed101e2274342f82_63c9ddb96dddae08d0ac69a8_63c9d6500c3d4b2fbeda7ac6_ExploroAd.jpeg', 'https://media-dev.exploro.com/inflight-media/barranquilla-colombia-.mp4', ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d09a892800ee0fb9bc66_barranquilla-overview_0.jpeg','https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d09a8928007ee3b9bc60_barranquilla-c3_0.jpeg','https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d09a89280035d9b9bc62_barranquilla-c4_0.jpeg'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d09a892800ad51b9bc5f_barranquilla-getting_0.jpeg','<p id="">There are many local attractions to explore all around Barranquilla. Getting around is up to the visitor and what they hope to accomplish while visiting this "party" city. Car rentals are available for long day trips and are around 150,000 pesos a day (USD 43). If you plan on venturing into a neighboring country (Panama and Venezuela are both just short drives away) a vehicle will be the easiest method of transportation. If you plan on staying in the city center, walking is a great way to explore the city and get a nice tan while soaking up the local culture and meeting friendly "Barranquilleros" along the way. Taxis are also plentiful and easy to flag down when traversing the city.</p>'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d09a8928001dd6b9bc63_barranquilla-fnb_0.jpeg','<p id="">In Barranquilla, there are several places to stop and enjoy the local cuisine. Local delicacies that you may want to try include arroz con coco (coconut rice) and sancocho de guandu (a soup made of pigeon peas and meat), bocachico frito (fried fish from the Magdalena River), and fried arepas and empanadas. All of these can be found at various Barranquillan restaurants and even a few street carts.</p>'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d09a8928006f00b9bc65_barranquilla-facts_0.jpeg','<p id="">The predominant local beer is Águila, which is, in fact, popular nationwide and is at a low price.Barranquilla was built in 1629 and developed slowly as a river port.Barranquilla is the Atlántico Department’s capital and the most important port in the country.The Carnival of Barranquilla is a popular folk and cultural event in Colombia that dates back to the 19th century.The first South American airline started in Barranquilla under the name of SCADTA. The airline has been in business since 1919 but changed its name to Avianca.Colombia is bordered by five countries (Venezuela, Brazil, Ecuador, Peru, and Panama) and two bodies of water (The Caribbean Sea and the Pacific Ocean).</p>'], ARRAY['Hotel Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod 