CLIMATE: Tropical

A city that means abode of peace, Dar Es Salaam is a meeting place and one of the two capitals of Tanzania. Found on the Indian Ocean coast, this beautiful fishing city manages to be the bustling hub of Tanzania while holding onto its friendly down-to-earth vibes. The city itself is built with international tourists in mind. The literal translation of “Dar” is home and the city enjoys a variety of cultures that have made this a special place to visit. Stop in for fresh fish, samosas, and the Indian, Arab, and African influences that have inundated themselves throughout the city.&nbsp;

There is nothing like traveling “home”, so you can rest assured when you visit Dar Es Salaam your needs will be met with the hospitality and friendly nature of the residents that truly make this destination a spot where everyone will enjoy spending time.

