Currency: Guatemala Quetzal

Guatemala City is the most populated city and capital of its country. It is found nestled in a mountain valley of the south-central part of Guatemala, its location resulting in spring-like temperatures throughout the year. Four volcanos are visible from the city, two presently active. The nearest volcano to Guatemala City is the Pacaya volcano, which occasionally erupts, sending ashy debris into the air. Its natural landscape speaks for itself, but Guatemala City’s downtown does its nation justice, with a rich culture home to art galleries, beautiful cathedrals and museums, trendy coffee shops, and fine eateries.', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d095886de89e82eea3f2_guatemala-city-c1_0.jpeg', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d095886de8df81eea3f3_guatemala-city-c2_0.jpeg', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63ca0aabed101e2274342f82_63c9ddb96dddae08d0ac69a8_63c9d6500c3d4b2fbeda7ac6_ExploroAd.jpeg', 'https://media-dev.exploro.com/inflight-media/guatemala-city-guatemala-.mp4', ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d095886de86245eea3f1_guatemala-city-overview_0.jpeg','https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d095886de83a0aeea3ef_guatemala-city-c3_0.jpeg','https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d095886de82aa4eea3ee_guatemala-city-c4_0.jpeg'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d095886de84c11eea3ed_guatemala-city-getting_0.jpeg','<p id="">In Guatemala City, chicken buses (recycled and repainted United States school buses) are a popular method of transport for locals, or, tourists that have seen them on TV. Otherwise, visitors can take shuttle buses, a slightly more expensive option, or hire a driver to get around the city. Or, there’s always our favorite option: to walk!</p>'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d095886de86ae3eea3f0_guatemala-city-fnb.jpeg','<p id="">Guatemala City has a great food scene full of richly seasoned dishes. Local staples include rice and beans, corn and flour tortillas and cheese, and grilled meats like pork, chicken, and beef. Fans of the tropical fruits and tostadas of Central America can find all of that and more. And the drinks flow pretty freely here too - perfect for those hot days (or nights) spent exploring everything this vibrant city has to offer.</p>'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d095886de844b0eea3f4_guatemala-city-facts_0.jpeg','<p id="">Present-day Guatemala City is the fourth permanent capital of the country. Schools close for ash days rather than snow days in Guatemala City. Guatemala is home to the tallest volcano in Central America. The city was originally located in what is now Antigua, Guatemala but was almost destroyed by an earthquake. Recently, Guatemala City’s metropolitan area has grown because it absorbed most of the neighboring municipalities, forming what is known as the Guatemala City Metropolitan Area. The current estimated population of Guatemala City is about one million, while its urban area is almost three million. As a result, it has the wealthiest and most powerful economy in the country by far.</p>'], ARRAY['Hotel Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum'], ARRAY['Restaurant Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commo