&nbsp;', 'Lakselv is in the Porsanger Municipality in Troms og Finnmark County, Norway. The village has only 2,283 people, yet it is still the administrative center and largest village.&nbsp;Many shops in Lakselv service the town’s people and the surrounding area. Lakselv Church can be found at the center of the village, a beautiful spot for visitors.The village is popular for Salmon, Trout, and Grayling fishing in the summer months. There are wonderful hiking opportunities in the Stabbursdalen National Park just west of the village. We encourage you to try a snowmobile safari or go skiing, ice fishing, and dog sledding during the winter. All are popular activities for visitors.&nbsp;', '', '', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63ca0aabed101e2274342f82_63c9ddb96dddae08d0ac69a8_63c9d6500c3d4b2fbeda7ac6_ExploroAd.jpeg', 'https://media-dev.exploro.com/inflight-media/lakselv-about-banner.jpg', ARRAY['','',''], ARRAY['','<p id="">You can arrive in Lakselv by air, rail or bus. Once in the village, transportation is available by taxi or a rental car. You can also rent bicycles in warmer weather, and the town is easily walkable.</p>'], ARRAY['','<p id="">There are many great restaurants and many different types of cuisine in Lakselv. However, if you want to try a well-known dish, we suggest trying Surkal (seasoned cabbage thinly sliced and slowly cooked), or Fiskeboller, a fish ball.</p>'], ARRAY['','<p id="">Lakselv has a temperate/maritime climate. Winters are cold, and summers are pleasant.The official language of Lakselv is Norwegian, but most Norwegians also speak English as a second language.Lakselv has a population of approximately 2,400.The currency in Lakselv is the Norwegian Krone.</p>'], ARRAY['Hotel Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequa