Among the Indian Ocean’s Lamu Archipelago off the East African coast floats the old trading port of Lamu Island, which holds the oldest continually inhabited city in Kenya. Lamu Old Town was first settled in the 12th century. Today, it’s a UNESCO World Heritage site and undiscovered Swahili beach destination where both Swahili and Islamic customs mingle to form a unique culture in and of itself. Lamu is different from other coastal cities due to an almost complete lack of automobiles. Instead, the townspeople travel between the Archipelago islands by boat. On land, they rely on donkeys to carry goods and cargo through the narrow stone streets. In Lamu you’ll find yearly cultural festivals, beautiful Islamic mosques for worship, and golden beaches without a throng of tourists', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d0924c894c76de64b6dd_lamu_lamu_island_kenya.jpeg', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d081caee12094487e881_carousel-2.jpeg', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63ca0aabed101e2274342f82_63c9ddb96dddae08d0ac69a8_63c9d6500c3d4b2fbeda7ac6_ExploroAd.jpeg', 'https://media-dev.exploro.com/inflight-media/lamu-hero-banner.jpg', ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d0924c894c4e2264b6e1_lamu_kenya_31579620455.jpeg','https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d081caee122c0387e87f_carousel-3.jpeg','https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d081caee12e7c187e880_carousel-4.jpeg'], ARRAY['',''], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d0924c894ce83864b6db_lamu-factimage.jpeg','<p id="">Lamu Town and its surrounding island offers coastal delicacies in spades. Every year Lamu holds a food festival (along with a yoga festival, a cultural festival, and a Muslim festival), but during the rest of the year you can always find fresh fish and produce at the market downtown. Here, you’ll also come across a variety of food stalls that sell everything from crabs and lobster to kebabs and samosa. Traditional Swahili food is typically eaten with your hands, but cutlery is readily available should you request it. Head to one of the restaurants on the seafront for delicious pizza and other more tourist-y foods, and wash it down with refreshing tamarind juice!</p>'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d0924c894c11a164b6dc_zein2.jpeg','<p id="">Swahili is the dominant language in Lamu.Due to its unique urban structure, culture, and historical significance, Kenya’s oldest existing town (Lamu Old Town) is a UNESCO World Heritage Site.The limestone and coral of Lamu’s 12th century buildings are often hailed as prominent examples of Swahili architecture, but the designs were also influenced by cultures from the Middle East, India, and Europe.Most of Lamu’s population practice Islam.The dhow fishing boats come from Arabic influence.The village of Shela is the more touristy part of the island where visitors come to shop, while Lamu Old Town is full of vintage history.</p>'], ARRAY['Hotel Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum'], ARRAY['Restaurant Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in c