Today, Lima is considered the political, cultural, financial, and commercial center of Peru. Because of Lima’s unique geography and climate, there is no shortage of unique things to do, see, and visit, making tourism one of Lima’s most significant sources of income. From water sports along the coast, to touring old Spanish architecture, to exploring the desert on an ATV, there are plenty of adventurous activities in Lima for visitors to enjoy.', 'Lima, Peru, is the nation’s capital and the pride and joy of Peru. Lima is located in the desert zone of region, in the valley of three rivers, and overlooks the Pacific Ocean. It is the fourth largest city in South America and has a population of approximately 10 million. Lima has a rich history and culture, including an array of historical monuments and stunning colonial architecture, making Lima a great place to explore for all visitors. In addition, you can enjoy first-class food, fantastic surfing, and exciting nightlife.', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d0857d5d8449a038b5e3_lima-c1.jpeg', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d0857d5d84bcfc38b5de_lima-c2.jpeg', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63ca0aabed101e2274342f82_63c9ddb96dddae08d0ac69a8_63c9d6500c3d4b2fbeda7ac6_ExploroAd.jpeg', 'https://media-dev.exploro.com/inflight-media/lima-peru.mp4', ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d0857d5d84171538b5dd_lima-overview.jpeg','https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d0857d5d8451cb38b5e0_lima-c3.jpeg','https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d0857d5d841ad438b5e2_lima-c4.jpeg'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d0857d5d84856538b5e1_lima-getting.jpeg','<p id="">Although Lima has a bus system and metro, many believe that the best way to see the city is by foot or bike. There are many bike paths throughout the city, and visitors can rent a bicycle in several areas throughout Lima. Practice your Spanish and chat with some of the locals, who are quite friendly and open and can give you great recommendations on where in the city to visit, eat, and stay!</p>'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d0847d5d84ee4238b5dc_lima-fnb.jpeg','<p id="">Lima offers local and international cuisines, with several restaurants where you can watch the chefs prepare your food with fresh, local ingredients such as produce, seafood, and beef. Be sure to order the ceviche apaltado:locally harvested fish cut into small cubes which are then marinated in fresh lime juice and served with fresh avocado, capers, olive oil and fresh basil.</p>'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d0857d5d848db138b5df_lima-facts.jpeg','<p id="">Lima’s nickname is "The City of Kings."Lima is the second-largest desert city in the world, second only to Cairo in Egypt.Lima has a lot of black vultures, but locals don’t mind, as they clean the city.In the 16th century, Lima had an issue with pirates, so they built the Real Filipe Fortress to respond to the attacks.In the Summer months, it can get up to 90 degrees Fahrenheit in Lima, whereas in the winter, it usually only drops to 54 degrees Fahrenheit.Lima spans over 1,032 square miles.</p>'], ARRAY['Hotel Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum'], ARRAY['Restaurant Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis no