African American culture flourished in the roots of Memphis and made the city what it is today. The jazz and blues scene Memphis is known for is a notable example of this. In 1977, Beale Street was declared the official ’Home of the Blues’ by an act of Congress, and many notable blues musicians like B.B. King and Bobby ’Blue’ Bland played on this street. Today, Memphis is still primarily known for its music scene, including Elvis Presley, the ’King of Rock and Roll.’ In addition to live music, Memphis visitors will fall in love with the fantastic BBQ the city offers and the many museums it boasts.', 'River-port Memphis is the second-most populous city in Tennessee and the fifth-most populous city in the Southeast. Its name originates from the first capital of ancient Egypt. One of the most historic and culturally significant cities in the Southern US, Memphis is considered the ’Birthplace of Rock ‘N’ Roll’ and ’Home of the Blues.’ Today, visitors enjoy the city’s bustling music scene, rich history, and fabulous restaurants.', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d071d021612e84c80b9b_memphis-c1.jpeg', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d071d02161054ac80b9e_memphis-c2.jpeg', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63ca0aabed101e2274342f82_63c9ddb96dddae08d0ac69a8_63c9d6500c3d4b2fbeda7ac6_ExploroAd.jpeg', 'https://media-dev.exploro.com/inflight-media/memphis-tennessee.mp4', ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d071d02161142bc80b9c_memphis-overview.jpeg','https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d071d0216185b8c80b9f_memphis-c3.jpeg','https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d071d02161761cc80b9a_memphis-c4.jpeg'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d071d0216154a9c80b9d_memphis-getting.jpeg','<p id="">Like many big cities, Memphis has a bus transportation system that can take visitors anywhere in the city. Additionally, the downtown area has a trolley system where visitors can pay $1 per ride or can purchase a $2 day pass. Uber, Lyft and taxis are also an available option to Memphis visitors.</p>'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d071d021611c75c80ba0_memphis-fnb.jpeg','<p id="">Memphis may be Tennessee’s Music City, but its mouthwatering gastronomy can’t go ignored. Barbecue is the official cuisine of Memphis, with "bbq" venues such as local favorite Central BBQ. You can’t go wrong with the ribs, pulled pork sandwich, or bbq nachos! Come for Southern staples like powdered-sugar beignets, fried chicken, and Tennessee whiskey. Beloved comfort foods and traditional recipes passed down over generations make up a cuisine responsible not only for drawing hungry tourists, but linking the community together.</p>'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d071d021612667c80ba1_memphis-facts.jpeg','<p id="">Mark Twain called Memphis the ’Good Samaritan City of the Mississippi.’ Memphis International Airport is the busiest cargo airport in the country. Beale Street is the most visited attraction in Tennessee. In 1966 Beale Street was declared a National Historic Landmark. Piggly Wiggly was founded in Memphis. Elvis Presley recorded at least 24 songs at Sun Studio.</p>'], ARRAY['Hotel Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum'], ARRAY['Restaurant Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim ven