&nbsp;', 'Molde is a coastal city in western Norway and is nicknamed the "City Of Roses" for the many roses found in the area. It is located on the Romsdal Peninsula and is surrounded by the Fannefjord and the Moldefjord. Molde grew into one of the largest timber trading ports in the 17th century and was charted as a municipality in 1838. Molde has seen steady growth since that time. Over the last ten years, the population has grown by 7.2%.&nbsp;', '', '', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63ca0aabed101e2274342f82_63c9ddb96dddae08d0ac69a8_63c9d6500c3d4b2fbeda7ac6_ExploroAd.jpeg', 'https://media-dev.exploro.com/inflight-media/molde-about-banner.jpg', ARRAY['','',''], ARRAY['','<p id="">Guests can arrive in Molde by air, train, or bus. Local transportation is available through taxis and car-sharing services.Visitor’s can explore the city by walking or biking.</p>'], ARRAY['','<p id="">There are many great restaurants in Molde, and many cuisines are available. If you are looking for a local dish try ordering the Farikal, a casserole consisting of mutton with cabbage cooked for several hours and served with boiled potatoes, or Torrfisk, a naturally dried Atlantic cod from any local restaurant.</p>'], ARRAY['','<p id="">Molde has a maritime/temperate climate. Winters are cold, and summers are pleasant.The official language in Molde is Norwegian, but most Norwegians also speak English as a second language.Molde has a population of 32,000, making it the 31st most populous municipality in Norway.The currency in Norway is called a Krone.Molde is nicknamed the "City of Roses."</p>'], ARRAY['Hotel Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur si