During the summer, this beach town is at its most popular. Each year the peak season is fully booked with concerts, farmer’s markets, surf competitions and more. Some favorite Myrtle Beach attractions include the musical acts at Legends in Concert, the sights at Broadway at the Beach, or the sealife at Ripley’s Aquarium. The outdoor Carolina Country Music Festival is hosted here each June, and you can visit the Myrtle Beach Convention Center for exciting exhibits, sports conventions, and other special events.', 'Recognizable by the big white Skywheel suspended over the Atlantic, South Carolina’s Myrtle Beach is a coastal tourist hub of the Southeast United States. Its mild weather and ample sunshine draw in millions of visitors each year to try some of the South’s best seafood, catch a live show, and tan on the warm sand. Go for a spin on the rides at the colorful beach boardwalk, attend one of the famous motorcycle rallies, or browse fancy boutiques at the Market Common downtown; Myrtle Beach has something for everyone.', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d071cae3dbceead34164_myrtle-c1.jpeg', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d071cae3db56b8d34162_myrtle-c2.jpeg', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63ca0aabed101e2274342f82_63c9ddb96dddae08d0ac69a8_63c9d6500c3d4b2fbeda7ac6_ExploroAd.jpeg', 'https://media-dev.exploro.com/inflight-media/myrtle-beach-south-carolina-.mp4', ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d071cae3db1239d34168_myrtle-overview.jpeg','https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d071cae3db615fd34163_myrtle-c3.jpeg','https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d071cae3db8a13d34167_myrtle-c4.jpeg'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d071cae3db599bd34166_myrtle-getting.jpeg','<p id="">So you’ve landed at the Myrtle Beach International Airport. What now? Most say the best way to get around Myrtle Beach is by car, and for visitors there are always taxi options as well as rideshare available. Bicycles, electric scooters and even golf carts are popular among locals and tourists to rent in the downtown district. The local bus system; Coast RTA,offers public transit with stops along Ocean Boulevard and Kings Highway, and unlimited day passes can be purchased for just $5.</p>'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d071cae3db7de9d34161_myrtle-fnb.jpeg','<p id="">Myrtle Beach is famous for its buffet-style seafood dinners and gorgeous waterfront-view restaurants, but it’s not your average coastal town. Like its neighboring states, Myrtle Beach stays true to its roots with familiar famous Southern dishes; juicy po’boys, seafood boils, chicken and grits, and of course, some great Carolina barbecue. If you prefer your sweet tea with something stronger, the city also features a variety of breweries, wineries, and award-winning cocktail bars.</p>'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d071cae3db209ed34165_myrtle-facts.jpeg','<p id="">The city’s name derives from the Wax Myrtle tree, a common local plant native to North and Central America as well as the Caribbean.There are approximately 425 hotels in the Myrtle Beach area.Within the "Grand Strand," there are over 60 miles of beaches.The climate here is subtropical and humid, with hot summers, mild winters, and autumnal tropical thunderstorms.Before Spanish arrival, the land was inhabited by the Native American Waccamaw and Winyah tribes.Often called the Golf Capital of the World, Myrtle Beach is home to over eighty golf courses.The Coastal Grand Mall is one of South Carolina’s largest indoor retail centers.</p>'], ARRAY['Hotel Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip 