Whether you are looking for a place to relax and soak up the sun, or an exciting place to explore and experience new things, Panama City offers experiences for all. The city is home to a number of museums and art galleries, as well as unique shops and restaurants. There are also many outdoor activities to enjoy, such as hiking, biking, and fishing.

If you are planning a visit to Panama City, be sure to check out all the city has to offer. You won’t be disappointed!', 'Welcome to Panama City, Florida! This sunny city is located on the Gulf of Mexico, making it a popular destination for beach lovers. With its white sand beaches and clear blue waters, it’s no wonder Panama City is referred to as having "The World’s Most Beautiful Beaches."

Panama City holds the best of Florida within the limits of a sunny lagoon getaway. It&nbsp;offers a variety of activities and attractions for visitors to enjoy: from seafood restaurants and nightlife, to golf courses and museums, there is something for everyone in Panama City. So whether you’re looking for a relaxing beach vacation or a fun-filled adventure, be sure to add Panama City, Florida to your travel list!', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d074892800d569b9b96e_panama-city-c1_0.jpeg', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d074892800ab91b9b972_panama-city-c2_0.jpeg', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63ca0aabed101e2274342f82_63c9ddb96dddae08d0ac69a8_63c9d6500c3d4b2fbeda7ac6_ExploroAd.jpeg', 'https://media-dev.exploro.com/inflight-media/panama-city-about-banner_0.jpg', ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d074892800d70cb9b974_panama-city-overview_0.jpeg','https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d0748928006434b9b970_panama-city-c3_0.jpeg','https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d074892800fb9cb9b973_panama-city-c4_0.jpeg'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d07489280070beb9b96f_panama-city-getting_0.jpeg','<p id="">Panama City is a large city, so getting around can be a bit daunting. Luckily, there are a number of transportation options available to help you get around.The best way to get around Panama City is by car. The city is very spread out, so having your own transportation will make it much easier to get around. If you are renting a car, be sure to get a map of the city so you can plan your route in advance.Another option for getting around Panama City is by bus. The city has an extensive public bus system that can take you to most places you want to go. The buses are reliable and reasonably priced, making this a great option for getting around.</p>'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d074892800548cb9b971_panama-city-fnb_0.jpeg','<p id="">Naturally, Panama City is famous for its amazing seafood. If you are looking for a quick bite to eat, there are plenty of fast food options available. However, if you want to sit down and enjoy a meal, there are also many restaurants that offer sit-down service.Panama City is also well known for its nightlife. There are a number of bars and clubs to choose from, so you can find the perfect spot to enjoy a night out on the town. If you are looking for a place to grab a drink during the day, there are a number of cafes and coffee shops that offer a variety of drinks, as well as a variety of snacks.</p>'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d07489280096f7b9b975_panama-city-facts_0.jpeg','<p id="">-Panama City was founded in 1909 by Finnish-American entrepreneur, George Merrick.-The city is named after the Panama Canal, which was completed in 1914.-Panama City is known as the "Seafood Capital of the South" due to the abundance of fresh seafood available.-The city is home to a number of festivals and events throughout the year, including the Panama City Beach Seafood and Music Festival, the Gulf Coast Jam, and Spring Break.-Panama City is home to one of the largest marinas in the world, St. Andrews Marina.-The average temperature in Panama City is 77 degrees Fahrenheit.-Panama City Beach was ranked as the #1 beach in the United States by TripAdvisor in 2016.</p>'], ARRAY['Hotel Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum'], ARRAY['