Puerto Vallarta’s economy relies heavily on tourism, and they do love their tourists.&nbsp;One place a lot of visitors flock to is the pink-and-white-flowered El Malecon; Puerto Vallarta’s boardwalk promenade. Here you can eat at the city’s best taquerias, browse the artsy Bohemian markets, and admire sculptures made by local artists.&nbsp;Elsewhere around the Bahía de Banderas (Bay of Flags), there are many sandy stretches, such as Playa Mismaloya, a sheltered cove with clear water suitable for snorkeling, and the Punta de Mita headland, a popular surfing spot.', 'Puerto Vallarta: everyone’s favorite resort and destination town. Stepping off the plane into the balmy ocean breeze, it immediately becomes apparent why this bright, summery getaway is so popular. You have all the time in the world on the sunny Mexican coast to wander the beach, hunt for a strawberry margarita, or walk the Cuale River downtown. Puerto Vallarta is famous for world-class resorts and electric nightlife, so between whale-watching and hiking up waterfalls you can relax or celebrate as much as your heart desires. Don’t forget to pack your sunscreen on your next trip to paradise on the Pacific coast.', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d08efa821769bb3ab90f_puerto-vallarta-c1.jpeg', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d08efa821766633ab90b_puerto-vallarta-c2.jpeg', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63ca0aabed101e2274342f82_63c9ddb96dddae08d0ac69a8_63c9d6500c3d4b2fbeda7ac6_ExploroAd.jpeg', 'https://media-dev.exploro.com/inflight-media/puerto-vallarta-mexico.mp4', ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d08efa821748e23ab90e_puerto-vallarta-overview.jpeg','https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d08efa82176d1b3ab90d_puerto-vallarta-c3.jpeg','https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d08dfa821717373ab90a_puerto-vallarta-c4.jpeg'], ARRAY['',''], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d08efa821706013ab910_puerto-vallarta-fnb.jpeg','<p id="">If you’re looking for great food and drink, you’ve come to the right place. Eat your weight in fish tostadas and shrimp ceviche, and don’t forget to browse the cocktail menu for a taste of Puerto Vallarta’s rich mixology scene. The undaunted tourist looking to expand their palette beyond the average tacos al pastor might schedule a famous Puerto Vallarta food/drink tastings for the finest flavors and spice. Ceviche, birria, mole, and various types of fried corn are just a few of the dishes you will not want to pass up. In between meals, visit one of the many frozen paleta vendors for a fresh fruit popsicle to cool yourself down in the heat of the sunshine.From casual taco stands and tropical beachfront palapas to upscale rooftop restaurants with panoramic views, dozens of restaurants are available to enjoy.</p>'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d08efa821795d93ab90c_puerto-vallarta-facts.jpeg','<p id="">Puerto Vallarta is cut in half by the Cuale River which separates the El Centro and Zona Romantica; two of what are generally considered the four/five major tourist zones in the city. These include the Marina Zone, the Hotel Zone, El Centro, and the Romantic Zone. The marina neighborhood comprises the marina and the area around the airport. Here, you can explore fun restaurants and boutiques while watching luxury yachts bob on the water.Further south, you’ll find most of Puerto Vallarta’s world-class resorts in the Hotel Zone. Beyond the ritzy hotels, there is an abundance of shopping galleries and beaches.You’ll probably spend a lot of time in El Centro, the historic downtown at the center of the city. Book some time for two of Puerto Valla’s must-dos; biking down the Malecòn and visiting the famed Nuestra Señora de Guadalupe church.Last but not least, the Romantic Zone is a general favorite and the nucleus of Puerto Va