&nbsp;', 'San Diego is known for its wonderful climate, 70 miles of pristine beaches, and wide variety of amusement parks that draw thousands of tourists every year. It is the most southern large city in California, lying just north of the U.S. border with Mexico, with a lot of Spanish influence.&nbsp;Palm-tree-decorated San Diego has become one of the largest tourist destinations in the USA. Visitors come for the lovely beaches, the many attractions, and the city’s relaxed atmosphere and people. Many activities and festivals all throughout the year, thanks to the mild weather, also add to the flow of tourists through San Diego.&nbsp;But most people come for their breathtaking sunsets and world-famous parks; among the most famous is the San Diego Zoo and Safari Park, SeaWorld San Diego, Belmont Park and LEGOLAND California, with LA Universal Studios and Disneyland just a day trip away.', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d07834ed267ed11c6cb7_san-diego-c1.jpeg', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d07834ed261b0e1c6cb5_san-diego-c2.jpeg', '', 'https://media-dev.exploro.com/inflight-media/san-diego.mp4', ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d07934ed2638931c6cc1_san-diego-overview.jpeg','https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d07834ed269f021c6cb3_san-diego-c3.jpeg','https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d07834ed269fcc1c6cb1_san-diego-c4.jpeg'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d07834ed26297d1c6cb4_san-diego-getting.jpeg','<p id="">A lot of tourists get around San Diego by renting a car if they don’t have their own with them. This way visitors are free to drive to as many of Southern California’s vacation destinations as they wish, and San Diego is right in the center of it all. Like most major cities, taxis and RideShare apps are popular to get around the city, and don’t forget to hop one one of the iconic, cherry-colored San Diego Trolleys for a trip around the town.</p>'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d07834ed2602ea1c6cb2_san-diego-fnb.jpeg','<p id="">San Diego is one of the top-rated U.S. cities to eat, so save your cheat days for your vacation here. Your taste buds will explode with the rich combination of United States and Latin American cuisines, like the California burrito and the Baja fish taco at beachy snack shacks around the city. Grab an acai bowl in the morning on your way out the door. Tip: surfing pairs great with Mexican food, and San Diego has the best around.</p>'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d07834ed268fa21c6cb6_san-diego-facts.jpeg','<p id="">The climate in San Diego is tropical. The summers are pleasant, and the winters are short and mild. It has been called California’s birthplace, since it was home to the first Spanish settlement. The population in San Diego is 1.56 million people. They also have the most dog-friendly restaurants in the U.S. per capita, so you can bring your furry friend on your trip to the beach. San Diego is one of the few places in the United States that naturally grows theTorrey Pine (the other place is also in Southern California, on Santa Rosa island); the rarest pine tree in the country and one of the rarest in the world. San Diego County produces approximately 60% of all California Avocados.</p>'], ARRAY['Hotel Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum'], ARRAY['Restaurant Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisci