usel-3.jpeg','https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d081caee12e7c187e880_carousel-4.jpeg'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d080caee1259cf87e87c_phuket-getting.jpeg','<p id="">When you arrive at the airport there are several shuttle services to choose from, or you can rent a taxi or an Uber, whose website states that you can request a ride up to 30 days in advance, at any time and on any day of the year. In addition to ride share there are also buses, cabs, and rentals to choose from.</p>'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d081caee12878f87e882_phuket-food.jpeg','<p id="">You really cannot go wrong with your food choice. Rich, delicate, simple, complex, you name it, and you can likely find it. Additionally, you can find all types of cuisine, including pizzerias, steak houses, seafood, and other healthy options. There are a large selection of restaurants including many of the popular chain options. Bars are open late, the wine and cheese are amazing, and there are dinner options for any pocketbook. There are many good restaurants to choose from in the area. You can find all types of cuisine, including pizzerias, steak houses, cafes, local eateries, seafood, and other healthy options. There are a large selection of restaurants including many of the popular chain options. Bars are open late, the seafood is fresh, and there are dinner options for any pocketbook.</p>'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d081caee128d0487e87d_phuket-fact.jpeg','<p id="">Phuket is the same distance from the equator as the African countries of Ethiopia and Nigeria and the South American countries of Venezuela and Colombia.	It is Thailand’s largest island covering around 576 square kilometres (222 square miles). It is around the same size as Singapore.	Phuket has around 36 beaches. Most of those on the west coast have crystal clear turquoise blue waters.	In 1974, the movie “The Man with the Golden Gun” was filmed on the island of Khao Phing Kan in Phang Nga Bay. From that point on the island was called James Bond Island.	The incredible Songkran water festival is in April, which marks the start of the Buddhist New Year.</p>'], ARRAY['Hotel Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum'], ARRAY['Restaurant Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum'], ARRAY['Attraction Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum'], ARRAY[''], 2, 1, 7, 1);
INSERT INTO city (name, slug, description_long, description_short, image_link, thumbnail_link, special_offer_image_link, video_link, gallery, getting_around, food_and_drink, facts, hotel, restaurant, attraction, shopping, featured_city, continent, country, region) VALUES ('Pittsburgh', 'pittsburgh', 'Pittsburgh has long been known for its waterways and natural resources and is historically known as the industrial center of a growing nation. The NFL Team purposefully played into that history with its name, the Steelers. As a meeting point for the Allegheny and Monongahela Rivers, which then becomes the Ohio River, the otherwise non-coastal Pittsburgh has water on multiple sides. Popularized initially as a significant industrial city, Pittsburgh has since transitioned into a destination with an economy focused on tourism, healthcare, and technology. Each professional sports team here shares the same black and gold colors to represent their city with pride.', 'Pittsburgh is a city with a lot of heart, located in the heart of southwestern Pennsylvania. The Steel City is a great place to visit, whether you’re interested in its history, its food, or its many cultural attractions. Pittsburgh’s downtown area is home to some of the best shopping and dining in the country, and its museums and theaters are world-renowned. Pittsburgh is also home to two professional sports teams, the Pittsburgh Steelers and the Pittsburgh Penguins, as well as the University of Pittsburgh. Surrounded by rolling hills and the Allegheny and Monongahela rivers, Pittsburgh is a beautiful place to live, work, and play.', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d07498ae6e521bf2741c_pittsburgh-c1.jpeg', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d07498ae6e73cdf2741b_pittsburgh-c2.jpeg', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63ca0aabed101e2274342f82_63c9ddb96dddae08d0ac69a8_63c9d6500c3d4b2fbeda7ac6_ExploroAd.jpeg', 'https://media-dev.exploro.com/inflight-media/pittsburgh-pennsylvania.mp4', ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d07498ae6e32bef27419_pittsburgh-overview.jpeg','https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d07498ae6e277cf2741d_pittsburgh-c3.jpeg','https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d07498ae6e57a5f2741e_pittsburgh-c4.jpeg'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d07498ae6e578cf2741a_pittsburgh-getting.jpeg','<p id="">Pittsburgh provides ample public transportation for visitors through 80+ bus and light rail routes that navigate the downtown and surrounding areas daily. The downtown district is the most easily accessible by foot, but rideshares are also available. Passenger rail is an option for visitors who want to travel further and provides a direct connection from Pittsburgh to Philadelphia, Chicago, Washington D.C., and New York City. </p>'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d07498ae6e301af27418_pittsburgh-fnb.jpeg','<p id="">Pittsburgh, PA, is a foodies paradise. Check out these 5 foods that are only available in Pittsburgh: the primanti sandwich; made with grilled meat, melted cheese, oil and vinegar coleslaw, tomato, and french fries between two massive slices of Italian bread. Pittsburgh is the only place to get the most authentic pierogies; handmade dumplings with a variety of delicious fillings. Be sure to check out the potato patch fries; fresh-cut fries topped with cheddar, bacon, vinegar, and brown gravy. Lastly, be sure to get your sweet on with the burnt almond torte, which is a classic in Pittsburgh.</p>'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d07498ae6e8e9bf2741f_pittsburgh-facts.jpeg','<p id="">Pittsburgh, the City of Bridges, has 446 bridges in total. Pittsburgh also has a huge number of stairs for any visitors looking to be a stair master. There are 700 unique sets of stairs located throughout the city and they are maintained by the Inspector of Steps. Seattle, known by many as a city in which it rains year-round, gets fewer rain and snow days than this city with its fluctuating weather.</p>'], ARRAY['Hotel Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum'], ARRAY['Restaurant Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum'], ARRAY['Attraction Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum'], ARRAY[''], 2, 1, 6, 1);
INSERT INTO city (name, slug, description_long, description_short, image_link, thumbnail_link, special_offer_image_link, video_link, gallery, getting_around, food_and_drink, facts, hotel, restaurant, attraction, shopping, featured_city, continent, country, region) VALUES ('Ponce', 'ponce', 'In 1508, Spanish conquistador Juan Ponce de Leon ventured into the territory known today as Ponce, Puerto Rico. In 1692, Ponce was named after the great-grandson of de Leon, Juan Ponce de Leon y Loayza. In the early 1800s, thousands of European immigrants migrated to the city under the Spanish Royal Decree of Graces in 1815, encouraging those living in countries friendly to Spain to settle in Puerto Rico. The only requirements were that they convert to Catholicism and agree to work in agriculture. Many of these migrants went on to make fortunes in the trade and export of sugar cane, cocoa, coffee, bananas, etc. The United States invaded Puerto Rico in 1898 during the Spanish-American War, and transferred the capital to San Juan. Ponce has the vibrant colors of San Juan with a sophisticated feel. It is known for its historical and cultural attractions, including historical museums, beautiful cathedrals, coffee plantations, and unique Ponce Creole architecture.', 'Ponce is Puerto Rico’s second most populated city behind San Juan. Often referred to as "La Perla del Sur," or The Pearl of the South, Ponce is located on Puerto Rico’s south coast and boasts numerous museums and cultural attractions. Located just three miles inland from the sea, Ponce borders the Central Mountain Range, allowing for spectacular views. No matter what month a visitor arrives in Ponce, there will surely be a cultural celebration as each month is dedicated to a carnival or festival honoring the island’s heritage.', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d07523f7407ef87b36ca_ponce-c1.jpeg', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d07523f7401aae7b36cb_ponce-c2.jpeg', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63ca0aabed101e2274342f82_63c9ddb96dddae08d0ac69a8_63c9d6500c3d4b2fbeda7ac6_ExploroAd.jpeg', 'https://media-dev.exploro.com/inflight-media/puerto_rico_live_boricua-1080p.mp4', ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d07523f74032bb7b36c9_ponce-overview.jpeg','https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d07523f7406f327b36ce_ponce-c3.jpeg','https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d07523f74050997b36cd_ponce-c4.jpeg'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d07523f740419d7b36cc_ponce-getting.jpeg','<p id="">Traveling around the downtown area of Ponce is accessible by foot; however, a vehicle is necessary to explore the wider region. You can rent a vehicle or opt to take a taxi.</p>'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d07523f7407f1d7b36c7_ponce-fnb.jpeg','<p id="">Piragua is a Puerto Rican shaved ice sweet treat popular in Ponce. Generally, the Piragua has a shape similar to a cone and is shaved ice covered in brightly colored, fruit-flavored syrups. Piraguas are typically sold in the street by pushcart vendors. Sample local Puerto Rican Rum if a more spirited dessert is desired. The Serralles family in Ponce produces Don Q, the most popular rum in the region.</p>'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d07523f740173d7b36c8_ponce-facts.jpeg','<p id="">Ponce is home to Puerto Rico’s oldest cemetery.Ponce has many educational options, including 77 public schools and 14 post-secondary colleges and universities.The city of Ponce has 31 barrios or wards.The most rainfall accumulated in Ponce falls in October and averages 6 inches.A passport is not necessary for U.S. citizens to visit Ponce, Puerto Rico.</p>'], ARRAY['Hotel Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum'], ARRAY['Restaurant Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum'], ARRAY['Attraction Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum'], ARRAY[''], 2, 1, 6, 1);
INSERT INTO city (name, slug, description_long, description_short, image_link, thumbnail_link, special_offer_image_link, video_link, gallery, getting_around, food_and_drink, facts, hotel, restaurant, attraction, shopping, featured_city, continent, country, region) VALUES ('Port-au-Prince', 'port-au-prince', 'Christopher Colombus visited the area around Port-au-Prince and claimed the land for Spain in 1492. Within a few years other European countries began to turn their eyes on Haiti and soon France gained control of Port-au-Prince and the area around the city. Due to the damage from the earthquake, the tourist industry in Port au-Prince declined for many years. Still, tourism is growing again, and Haiti’s 1,000 miles of coastline and beautiful, award-winning beaches are attracting visitors worldwide. Haiti has new hope and a bright future as the community steps forward to rebuild their country. More has been accomplished in the 12 years since the earthquake than in the 100 years preceding the disaster. Still, the city’s history and culture is not forgotten; reflected in its many museums and historical sites.', 'Haiti and the Dominican Republic both share the Caribbean Island of Hispaniola. The western part of the Island comprises the country of Haiti, where Port-au-Prince is the capital. Nearly half the population of Haiti lives in Port-au-Prince. You can tour the Haitian museum to learn about Haitian history, check out flea markets like the Marche de Fer, spend time on Etang Saumatre, the largest lake in Haiti, check out the rum distillery, and travel into the mountains to Fort Jacques; the National Park. Port-au-prince is known for its lively nightlife, with a variety of bars and clubs to keep you entertained into the early hours of the morning. And of course, there are plenty of beaches and parks to relax in the heat and gorgeous landscapes of Haiti.', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d095886de84265eea3e8_port-au-prince-c1.jpeg', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d095886de852fceea3e3_port-au-prince-c2.jpeg', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63ca0aabed101e2274342f82_63c9ddb96dddae08d0ac69a8_63c9d6500c3d4b2fbeda7ac6_ExploroAd.jpeg', 'https://media-dev.exploro.com/inflight-media/port-au-prince-haiti-.mp4', ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d095886de886c1eea3e7_port-au-prince-overview.jpeg','https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d095886de8ba31eea3e6_port-au-prince-c3.jpeg','https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d095886de8ecebeea3e9_port-au-prince-c4.jpeg'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d095886de87a61eea3ea_port-au-prince-getting.jpeg','<p id="">In Haiti, 76% of residents walk wherever they need to go. If you want to rent a cab, it’s important to negotiate a price with the driver before your ride as there is no set fee; drivers can charge whatever they choose to charge. The closest thing to public transportation in Haiti is a minibus the local population calls a tap-tap.</p>'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d095886de838edeea3e5_port-au-prince-fnb.jpeg','<p id="">Port-au-prince has wonderful cuisine that is a mixture of the different cultures in Haiti, from Haitian, Creole to French fare, all mixed with flavorful spices. So whether you’re looking for something spicy or something sweet, you’ll be able to find it in this city. Eat your weight in classic Haitian Gumbo, andbe sure to try the Haitian national dish of rice and beans. This hearty meal is usually served with a side of fried plantains, and it’s the perfect way to fill up after a long day of exploring Port-au-Prince.</p>'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d095886de8feb2eea3e4_port-au-prince-facts.jpeg','<p id="">The climate of Port-au-Prince is tropical. Winters are short and mild and summers are long, hot, and humid.The currency used in Haiti is called the Gourde. Currently, 1 US Dollar equals 132.94 Haitian Gourde.The population of Haiti was 11.4 million residents in 2020.The language in Haiti is French, but many residents speak English as a second language.Haiti was discovered by Christopher Colombus in 1492.Haiti means ’land of the mountains’.Voodoo is recognized as a religion in Haiti.Haiti was the first country in the western world to abolish slavery.</p>'], ARRAY['Hotel Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum'], ARRAY['Restaurant Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum'], ARRAY['Attraction Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum'], ARRAY[''], 2, 1, 33, 1);
INSERT INTO city (name, slug, description_long, description_short, image_link, thumbnail_link, special_offer_image_link, video_link, gallery, getting_around, food_and_drink, facts, hotel, restaurant, attraction, shopping, featured_city, continent, country, region) VALUES ('Portland-Maine', 'portland-maine', 'Portland received its name from the English Isle of Portland. The area where Portland sits today was founded as a trading post for fishers and was first named Casco. It was anointed the state’s capital in 1820 when Maine entered the U.S. as a state. The city was destroyed by fire multiple times during the past 200 years. Each time it burned, Portland was rebuilt, which is why the city seal depicts a phoenix rising from the ashes. Portland is southern Maine’s cultural, economic, and tourism center. One of five residents has a job supporting tourism. Discover Maine’s maritime history, forts along the coast, lighthouses, and top-rated restaurants. You’ll find world-class writers and artists in this hot spot of American creativity with its cozy setting and sense of community.', 'Portland is in the state of Maine, set on a peninsula extending into Casco Bay. The Old Port, the city’s original location, has several working fishing docks, and many warehouses are now shops, restaurants, bars, and nightclubs. In the 2020 Census, Maine had a population of 67,000, making it one of the largest cities in New England. Portland is the center of tourism, economy, and growth along the southern coast of Maine. The city has beautiful cobblestone streets, trendy restaurants, red-brick buildings, epic lighthouses, craft breweries, and fishing piers. Let’s not forget all the lobster and lobster rolls you can eat. Come check it all out!', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d0750bec5cf6e7b8560e_portland-maine-c1.jpeg', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d0760bec5c5c7ab85617_portland-maine-c2.jpeg', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63ca0aabed101e2274342f82_63c9ddb96dddae08d0ac69a8_63c9d6500c3d4b2fbeda7ac6_ExploroAd.jpeg', 'https://media-dev.exploro.com/inflight-media/portland-maine-about-banner.jpg', ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d0760bec5c84f6b85610_portland-maine-overview.jpeg','https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d0750bec5c450bb8560f_portland-maine-c3.jpeg','https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d0760bec5cf761b85611_portland-maine-c4.jpeg'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d0750bec5c0b54b8560d_portland-maine-getting.jpeg','<p id="">Portland is a very walkable city. However, having a car is a great option to get around the spread-out areas of the region. If you don’t have your vehicle, rentals are available by the day or week. Additionally, Portland has a trolly system that circles the city. Uber and Lyft are also available in Portland.</p>'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d0750bec5ce268b85609_portland-maine-fnb.jpeg','<p id="">Portland has developed a reputation for its food because of its excellent restaurants. Although you can find any food you could ever want, the city is mainly known for its fresh seafood. A local favorite is The Highroller Lobster Company. Here, you will eat one of the best lobsters of your life.</p>'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d0760bec5c1242b85612_portland-maine-facts.jpeg','<p id="">The official language in Portland is English.The climate in Portland is continental. Winters are cold and wet, and summers are mild and pleasant.The currency in Portland is the U.S. Dollar.The elevation of Portland is 62 feet.The first settlers arrived in Portland in 1632.The city was incorporated on July 4, 1786.</p>'], ARRAY['Hotel Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqu