is Norwegian, but most residents speak English as a second language.The currency of Stokmarknes is the Norwegian Krone.One of the happiest countries in the world is Norway.Norway is one of the cleanest countries in the world.You can still see polar bears in the wild in Norway.</p>'], ARRAY['Hotel Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum'], ARRAY['Restaurant Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum'], ARRAY['Attraction Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum'], ARRAY[''], 2, 1, 14, 1);
INSERT INTO city (name, slug, description_long, description_short, image_link, thumbnail_link, special_offer_image_link, video_link, gallery, getting_around, food_and_drink, facts, hotel, restaurant, attraction, shopping, featured_city, continent, country, region) VALUES ('Svolvaer', 'svolvaer', 'The best times to visit the Lofoten Islands are spring, summer, and fall; the winter months are dark on most days. The dark months, however, give visitors and residents a special and unique vantage point to see the northern lights. The summer has long sunny days; winter is long and dark. Svolvaer is the principal community of the islands and is a popular stop on the Norwegian Coastal Voyage, so most tourists end up here. When you first see Svolvaer, the snow-capped peaks are dramatic and gorgeous. We encourage you to explore the museums and cultural places in Svolvaer and to enjoy great food at the restaurants and pubs. It is a dreamy, charming little village.', 'Svolvaer is 95 miles north of the Arctic Circle and 800 miles from Oslo. The Lofoten archipelago is known for its rugged beauty. Painters and authors have long been inspired by the islands, which appear in many Norwegian paintings and the work of Jules Verne. The compact city has many art museums and locations to view various art installations and multiple cafes. It is also a great stop to buy supplies for those in neighboring smaller Nordic towns known for being low-key. If you are here for a couple of nights, see the famous puffer birds that call this area home. The landscape is beautiful, with majestic mountains rising out of the sea, beaches bordered by fjords, and small fishing towns sprinkled along the coast. Svolvaer has been called one of the most beautiful areas in northern Norway.', '', '', '', 'https://media-dev.exploro.com/inflight-media/svolvaer-about-banner.jpg', ARRAY['','',''], ARRAY['','<p id="">Svolvaer is a compact city, so the best thing you can do is walk around to get where you want to go. However, renting a car to get into the city may be best, as you go through several islands to get there. A ferry is also available. The main takeaway is that it takes effort and time to get to Svolvaer. In town, public transportation is available, as well as taxis, but on foot is the best vantage point to take in the city.</p>'], ARRAY['','<p id="">Svolvaer offers many food choices, and prices range from budget-friendly to expensive. One of the town’s top restaurants is Borsen, a former fish house. Their specialties are stockfish and Lofoten Lamb. While in Svolvaer, we suggest a tour of Lofotpils, a Norwegian microbrewery, to enjoy tasting some locally crafted beers.</p>'], ARRAY['','<p id="">Atlantic Cod fisheries, particularly during winter, have remained one of the town’s most critical economic foundations.Svolvaer became a "town" in 1996.Sheltered by mountains to the west and north, the Svolvaer area has less fog and experiences higher daytime temperatures in summer than in the western part of Lofoten, a neighboring city.It is in Midsummer that you can see the midnight sun.The “Svolvaer Goat” (Svolvaergeita) is a mountain with two characteristics “horns” that are popular among climbers.</p>'], ARRAY['Hotel Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum'], ARRAY['Restaurant Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum'], ARRAY['Attraction Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum'], ARRAY[''], 2, 1, 14, 1);
INSERT INTO city (name, slug, description_long, description_short, image_link, thumbnail_link, special_offer_image_link, video_link, gallery, getting_around, food_and_drink, facts, hotel, restaurant, attraction, shopping, featured_city, continent, country, region) VALUES ('Tampa', 'tampa', 'World-class beaches on the Gulf Coast, theme parks, sports teams, and hot-humid weather that includes thunderstorms are just a few things Tampa Bay is well-known for. Enjoy a walk along the longest sidewalk in the world or in Cuban neighborhoods with an active nightlife. Find rich history and lots of things to do in a city that screams of beauty and cultural experiences for the tourists and locals alike. Tampa is currently occupied primarily by retirees, thanks to its laid-back charm that emanates from the city streets. However, the younger crowds are drawn in by warm sunny beaches, that create a perfect destination for spring break or a fall getaway.', 'If you’re looking for a beach vacation, Tampa is a perfect spot to explore. Offering cool vibes and unique flavors, Tampa plays home to the Cuban sandwich, Spanish bean soup, and deviled crab, just to start. This means you won’t be left short-handed when it comes to exploratory food options. Early afternoon breezes on the bay mixed with the frequency of thunderstorms help keep temperatures under 100 degrees. Tampa is actually known as the lightning capital of the world, so if you are visiting in the summers, keep an eye out for storms on the horizon. Whether you are just looking for a spot to enjoy the beach or a city with a bit of everything, Tampa might be the destination for you.', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d07d23f74004587b36ec_tampa-c1.jpeg', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d07d23f7407dc07b36ee_tampa-c2.jpeg', '', 'https://media-dev.exploro.com/inflight-media/tampa-florida-.mp4', ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d07d23f740065b7b36f0_tampa-overview.jpeg','https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d07c23f7400ecb7b36eb_tampa-c3.jpeg','https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d07d23f740cce57b36ef_tampa-c4.jpeg'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d07c23f74085677b36e9_tampa-getting.jpeg','<p id="">Tampa runs without a subway system, but there is a bus system that meets the needs of tourists and residents. People can rent taxis by hour, day, or week. Trolleys travel set routes in the city, and passengers can jump off or on the trolleys at every stop. Uber and Lyft are also available in Tampa and are a great and inexpensive way to get around. Renting a bicycle or using your feet as transportation are other popular ways to get around the city.</p>'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d07d23f7405d537b36ed_tampa-fnb.jpeg','<p id="">Tampa is a cultural dream in terms of food. With everything from Spanish Bean Soup to Cuban sandwiches, deviled crab, and interesting guava-inspired dishes, there is so much to choose from you’ll love the flavors and styles of food in this city by the Bay.</p>'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d07c23f7402a8e7b36ea_tampa-facts.jpeg','<p id="">If you are looking for a city that is warm in both temperature and neighborly kindness, Tampa is the destination for you. Visit Tampa to experience the gorgeous beaches, and hip social neighborhoods as well as a cultural experience that stands out above the others in the area. Its past is a storied one, with the first scheduled flight landing in Tampa after flying from St. Petersburg to the Cuban cigars that made their home in Ybor City. Fort Brooke was once an established part of the Tampa Bay area and was originally constructed as a means of protecting the vulnerable and strategic harbor from attack. Tampa was historically settled by Cuban and Spanish immigrants, and employment was almost entirely industrial in the early days of Tampa’s history. Today the economy is driven by tourism, healthcare, and finance.</p>'], ARRAY['Hotel Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum'], ARRAY['Restaurant Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum'], ARRAY['Attraction Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur sint occaecat cupidatat non proident, sunt in culpa qui officia deserunt mollit anim id est laborum'], ARRAY[''], 2, 1, 6, 1);
INSERT INTO city (name, slug, description_long, description_short, image_link, thumbnail_link, special_offer_image_link, video_link, gallery, getting_around, food_and_drink, facts, hotel, restaurant, attraction, shopping, featured_city, continent, country, region) VALUES ('Tawau', 'tawau', 'Tawau was formerly known as Tawao. It is the capital of the Tawau District in Sabah, Malaysia. It is the third-largest city in Sabah, coming in behind Kota Kinabalu and Sandakan. It is situated on the Semporna Peninsula and surrounded by beautiful nature areas, conservation areas, and national parks. The town proper had an estimated population (as of 2010) of 113,809. However, there are nearly 400,000 people living in and around the city. The main economic activities of the town are cocoa, timber, palm oil plantations, and prawn farming.', 'Tawau really took off in the 1980’s and the population has grown greatly since then. Tawau became an attractive area after the formation of its lumber and cocoa farming industry, which keeps things busy and active today. The area has a rich history, at one point being a disputed territory between the British and the Dutch. In 1944 Tawau was completely destroyed by allied bombing raids. The city was rebuilt three years later, in 1947. The climate is relatively hot and wet with average shade temperature about 26 °C (79 °F), with 29 °C (84 °F) at noon and falling to around 23 °C (73 °F) at night.', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d09198ae6e2202f27e63_tawau-carousel1.jpeg', 'https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d09198ae6e5475f27e5e_tawau-carousel2.jpeg', '', 'https://media-dev.exploro.com/inflight-media/about-tawau-banner.jpg', ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d09198ae6e54e6f27e60_tawau-overview.jpeg','https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d09198ae6e7581f27e5d_tawau-carousel3.jpeg','https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d09198ae6eea17f27e62_tawau-carousel4.jpeg'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d09198ae6efdd3f27e5c_tawau-getting.jpeg','<p id="">When you arrive at the airport there are some shuttle services to choose from, or you can rent a taxi or a Grab, which is the region’s version of an Uber and operates similarly. Taxi fares around town would cost around RM5. The bus is also a fair option, and will cost much less, around RM 2 to travel around town and out to the rural areas like Balung and Merotai.</p>'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d09198ae6e3c92f27e61_tawau-food.jpeg','<p id="">Tawau has delicious food but not as many options as some larger towns in Malaysia. However, you really cannot go wrong with your food choice. Chinese, Malay, and Thai foods are prominent, and seafood is a main component in many of those dishes. Tofu noodles, a classic Sabahan breakfast, is something we recommend you seek out. They are delicious noodles served with several variations of tofu sauce.</p>'], ARRAY['https://uploads-ssl.webflow.com/63be358a2ba7e25fed479661/63c8d09198ae6ef121f27e5f_tawau-facts.jpeg','<p id="">Tawau is the 3rd biggest city in Sabah after Kota Kinabalu and Sandakan.	Located only 30 minutes from the Philippines.	The Malaysian Census 2010 Report indicates that the whole Tawau municipality area has a total population of 397,673.	The people of Tawau mainly speak Malay, with a distinct Sabahan creole.	As most Tawau Chinese are Hakka Chinese, Hakka Chinese is widely spoken.	Tawau’s mean rainfall varies from 1800 mm to 2500 mm.</p>'], ARRAY['Hotel Tab Heading','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur. Excepteur si